## Description {#details}

This file defines the RefCountedBase, ThreadSafeRefCountedBase, and IntrusiveRefCntPtr classes.

IntrusiveRefCntPtr is a smart pointer to an object which maintains a reference count. (ThreadSafe)RefCountedBase is a mixin class that adds a refcount member variable and methods for updating the refcount. An object that inherits from (ThreadSafe)RefCountedBase deletes itself when its refcount hits zero.

For example:


<ProgramListing>

<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight">MyClass : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> RefCountedBase&lt;MyClass&gt; &#123;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> foo() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Constructing an IntrusiveRefCntPtr increases the pointee&#39;s refcount</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// by 1 (from 0 in this case).</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;MyClass&gt; Ptr1(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">new</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MyClass());</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Copying an IntrusiveRefCntPtr increases the pointee&#39;s refcount by 1</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;MyClass&gt; Ptr2(Ptr1);</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Constructing an IntrusiveRefCntPtr has no effect on the object&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// refcount.  After a move, the moved-from pointer is null.</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;MyClass&gt; Ptr3(std::move(Ptr1));</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(Ptr1 == </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">nullptr</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Clearing an IntrusiveRefCntPtr decreases the pointee&#39;s refcount by 1</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  Ptr2.reset();</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The object deletes itself when we return from the function, because</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Ptr3&#39;s destructor decrements its refcount to 0</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>

</ProgramListing>


You can use IntrusiveRefCntPtr with isa&lt;T&gt;(), dyn&#95;cast&lt;T&gt;(), etc.:


<ProgramListing>

<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;MyClass&gt; <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/targetlibraryinfo-cpp/#aca185e6d0e9f423dbb24440206454872a11dbf501abf829b3ab7049c2d3a8a053">Ptr</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">new</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MyClass());</span></CodeLine>
<CodeLine><span class="doxyHighlight">OtherClass &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/codeview/#a5998c3d968454cd19d6c0ba8e5331a14a6311ae17c1ee52b36e68aaf4ad066387">Other</a> = dyn&#95;cast&lt;OtherClass&gt;(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/targetlibraryinfo-cpp/#aca185e6d0e9f423dbb24440206454872a11dbf501abf829b3ab7049c2d3a8a053">Ptr</a>);  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Ptr.get() not required</span></CodeLine>

</ProgramListing>


IntrusiveRefCntPtr works with any class that


<ul>
<li>inherits from (ThreadSafe)RefCountedBase,</li>
<li>has <a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#ga8bf6836a2bd83d4d7a9c8ac79d3da011">Retain()</a> and Release() methods, or</li>
<li>specializes IntrusiveRefCntPtrInfo.</li>
</ul>

<Link id="l00141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="141"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Class you can specialize to provide custom retain/release functionality for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// a type.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="143"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="144"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Usually specializing this class is not necessary, as IntrusiveRefCntPtr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="145"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// works with any type which defines Retain() and Release() functions -- you</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="146"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// can define those functions yourself if RefCountedBase doesn&#39;t work for you.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="147"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="148"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// One case when you might want to specialize this type is if you have</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="149"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  - Foo.h defines type Foo and includes Bar.h, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  - Bar.h uses IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;Foo&gt; in inline functions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="151"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="152"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Because Foo.h includes Bar.h, Bar.h can&#39;t include Foo.h in order to pull in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="153"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the declaration of Foo.  Without the declaration of Foo, normally Bar.h</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// wouldn&#39;t be able to use IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;Foo&gt;, which wants to call</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// T::Retain and T::Release.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// To resolve this, Bar.h could include a third header, FooFwd.h, which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// forward-declares Foo and specializes IntrusiveRefCntPtrInfo&lt;Foo&gt;.  Then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Bar.h could use IntrusiveRefCntPtr&lt;Foo&gt;, although it still couldn&#39;t call any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// functions on Foo itself, because Foo would be an incomplete type.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/intrusiverefcntptrinfo"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> T&gt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/intrusiverefcntptrinfo">IntrusiveRefCntPtrInfo</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/intrusiverefcntptrinfo/#a164f355991617c24c14e4d61cf2787da"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/intrusiverefcntptrinfo/#a164f355991617c24c14e4d61cf2787da">useCount</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a> &#42;obj) &#123; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> obj-&gt;UseCount(); &#125;</span></CodeLine>
